data.title: Full Match | Hangzhou Spark vs Guangzhou Charge | Overwatch League 2020 | Week 8 | Day 2
data.description: Week 8 of the 2020 Overwatch League season is live on March 28 and March 29 on YouTube Gaming. The two days of matches feature the Guangzhou Charge, Shanghai Dragons, Chengdu Hunters, Hangzhou Spark, Toronto Defiant, Boston Uprising, Los Angeles Valiant, Seoul Dynasty, San Francisco Shock, Los Angeles Gladiators, Florida Mayhem, and Atlanta Reign. Will the Shock build on their win earlier this season and start to replicate last season's success? Which of the teams making their season debuts will start off the strongest? Tune in to find out!

data.title: Top 5 Plays of Week 5: Jjonak's Instant Sleep Dart Is on Target
data.description: The first week of Hero Pool produced a spectacle of pure chaos in Washington, D.C. We got a lot of Sombra play, which meant a lot of Jjonak hitting unthinkable Sleep Darts. Winston got his time to shine and Roar made sure to capitalize on Eichenwalde. Meanwhile, Blass Doomfist continued to reign supreme.

data.title: Full Match | Boston Uprising vs Atlanta Reign | Overwatch League 2020 | Week 5 | Day 2
data.description: Week 5 of the 2020 Overwatch League season is live from Washington D.C. on March 7 and March 8 on YouTube Gaming. The two-day homestand features the Toronto Defiant, Florida Mayhem, Paris Eternal, Houston Outlaws, Boston Uprising, Philadelphia Fusion, New York Excelsior and Atlanta Reign. Will the Fusion put down Paris Eternal to remain undefeated? Can the Justice make up for their last homestand and win at home? Tune in to find out!

data.title: Justice GM Analynn Dang: Dont Let Other People Tell You That You Dont Belong Here
data.description: Washington Justice General Manager Analynn Dang talks about her career in esports, International Womens Day, her passion for Overwatch, and shares her advice for women looking to join the industry.

data.title: Top 5 Plays of Week 4: A Blas of Glory
data.description: Another week of #OWL2020 is in the books, and it did not disappoint! Blass Doomfist helped the Outlaws secure their first win, Pharah made a triumphant return to Ilios, and once again we are reminded to give thanks to Mr. Logix for his beautiful Tracer play!
